.TH AILAB 1 "2026" "ailab" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ailab \- manage LXD-based sandboxes for running AI tools safely on Ubuntu
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ailab
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ailab
creates lightweight LXD containers pre-wired to use AI services running
on the host (lemonade-server, ollama). Each container shares the user's
home directory while keeping installed software isolated. All containers
live in a dedicated LXD project named \fBailab\fR.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B new \fINAME\fR [\-\-install \fIPACKAGE\fR] [\-\-port \fIHOST:CONTAINER\fR]
Create a new sandbox container. Optionally install one or more packages
immediately after creation; packages with an onboard step run it
automatically, then an interactive shell is opened.
.TP
.B run \fINAME\fR
Start the container (if stopped) and open an interactive login shell.
.TP
.B stop \fINAME\fR
Stop a running container.
.TP
.B list
List all ailab containers with status, IP address, and forwarded ports.
Alias: \fBls\fR
.TP
.B delete \fINAME\fR [\-\-force]
Stop and permanently delete a container. Prompts for confirmation unless
\fB\-\-force\fR is given.
Alias: \fBrm\fR
.TP
.B install \fINAME PACKAGE\fR
Install a pre-configured AI tool into an existing container. Tools are
configured for local-first AI with cloud providers disabled.
.TP
.B packages
List available installable packages.
Alias: \fBpkgs\fR
.TP
.B port add \fINAME PORT\fR [\fICONTAINER_PORT\fR] [\-\-inbound]
Add a port proxy to a container. Default: outbound (host browser to
container service). With \fB\-\-inbound\fR: container localhost to host service.
.TP
.B port remove \fINAME PORT\fR
Remove a custom port proxy.
.TP
.B port list \fINAME\fR
List all port proxies on a container.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create a sandbox with openclaw, run onboarding, drop to shell:
.B ailab new mybox \-\-install openclaw
.TP
List all sandboxes:
.B ailab list
.TP
Open a shell in an existing sandbox:
.B ailab run mybox
.TP
Stop a running sandbox:
.B ailab stop mybox
.TP
Install nullclaw into an existing sandbox:
.B ailab install mybox nullclaw
.TP
Expose a port from the container to the host:
.B ailab port add mybox 9000
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/ailab/containers/NAME/
Per-container configuration directory. Accessible inside the container
at the same path via the bind-mounted home directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lxc (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Ken VanDine and contributors.
Homepage: https://github.com/lemonade-sdk/ailab
